# Dagster orchestration and partitions

## Naming

- **Jobs**: follow `docs/dagster_jobs.md`: `<layer_scope>__<domain_or_source>__<cadence>_job`.
- **Schedules**: same stem: `<layer_scope>__<domain_or_source>__<cadence>_schedule`.

## Partition strategy (do not blur tiers)

- **Tier 1 staging**: minute-partitioned, **append-only** ingest assets (raw staging).
  - Schedules must anchor to the **last completed minute** (avoid windows ending “in the future”).
- **Tier 2 canonical**: hourly-partitioned, **recomputable** assets across layers (raw→bronze→silver→gold→quality→reports).
  - Canonical runs overwrite the hourly partition outputs deterministically.

## Window semantics

- Treat all windows as **UTC** and **[start,end)**.
- For canonical hourly raw, ensure metadata includes `window_start_utc`, `window_end_utc`, and whether it was `staging_compaction` vs `api_backfill`.

## Backfill / incomplete-hour behavior

- Canonical hourly raw assets may compact staging microbatches **or** fetch via API fallback when expected microbatch slots are missing.
- If you change fallback logic, update the operational contract in `docs/dagster_jobs.md`.

## Partition-compatible jobs

- Dagster asset jobs must select assets with the **same partitions definition**.
- If you need a “full stack” job, provide partition-compatible manual entrypoints (don’t mix minute + hourly in one job).

